comments: James (LAL) legally contests Morant (MEM) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Anderson (MEM) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to LAL.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) briefly places his hands on Anthony (LAL) as Anthony sets the pick and disengages as he hedges outward.
Anthony (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Anderson's (MEM) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.

Replay review of the foul called on Anderson (MEM) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful. Anderson (MEM) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt when he makes incidental "high-five" contact. Anderson also makes incidental lower-body contact as James seeks the contact by kicking his leg abnormally.
Anderson (MEM) moves from his designated spot prior to the jump ball.
Anderson (MEM) is already in Bradley's (LAL) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Westbrook (LAL) is established in Morant's (MEM) path when marginal body contact occurs as Morant spins on his gather.
James (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball during Morant's (MEM) put-back shot attempt.
James (LAL) places a bent forearm on Anderson's (MEM) front as he braces for the contact and releases away.
Anderson (MEM) is trailing Monk (LAL) when marginal lower-body contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) moves his pivot foot heel-to-toe to create space.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Bradley's (LAL) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Bradley (LAL) makes contact to Morant's (MEM) arm during his rip-through that affects his SQBR.
Westbrook (LAL) is jumping alongside Morant's (MEM) path when marginal body contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) makes marginal contact to James (LAL) as they pursue the loose ball.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) legally contest Bradley's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Bane's (MEM) left foot lands out of bounds while he maintains control of the ball. The possession is correctly awarded to LAL.
James (LAL) does not establish a legal screening position in Anderson's (MEM) path as he delivers contact during the screen.
Anderson (MEM) makes contact with Anthony's (LAL) arm that affects his ability to gather the inbound pass.
Anthony (LAL) is already in Bane's (MEM) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Anderson (MEM) slides his hand across and off James' (LAL) upper body at the start of the drive, and the contact is marginal.
Westbrook (LAL) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM).
